{
  "texts": [
    "Concerning submitting unanonymized data, 70 respondents were amenable to sharing medical history, and 18 didn't mind to share demographic data.",
    "However, no respondents advocated the sharing of medical record numbers without anonymization.",
    "Additional comments are displayed in Table 3.",
    "In summary, integrating AI in healthcare, primarily through tools such as ChatGPT, poses reliability, privacy, and practicality challenges.",
    "Although AI proves helpful for general tasks, its limitations in specialized medical settings and concerns regarding the privacy and safety of patient data highlight the necessity for prudent application and specialized training for healthcare practitioners."
  ]
}